<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idc3e0fdad-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87" identifier="/us/usc/t38/s5704"><num value="5704">§ 5704.</num><heading> Transcript of trial records</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary may purchase transcripts of the record, including all evidence, of trial of litigated cases.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idc3e0fdae-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87">(<ref href="/us/pl/85/857">Pub. L. 85–857</ref>, <date date="1958-09-02">Sept. 2, 1958</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/72/1237">72 Stat. 1237</ref>, § 3304; renumbered § 5704, <ref href="/us/pl/102/40/tIV/s402/b/1">Pub. L. 102–40, title IV, § 402(b)(1)</ref>, <date date="1991-05-07">May 7, 1991</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/105/238">105 Stat. 238</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/102/83/s4/b/1">Pub. L. 102–83, § 4(b)(1)</ref>, (2)(E), <date date="1991-08-06">Aug. 6, 1991</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/105/404">105 Stat. 404</ref>, 405.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idc3e0fdaf-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87">
